==English==
===Etymology===
Late Latin, from Greek [[πληθορη]] ‘fullness’, from [[πληθειν]] ‘to be full’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-plethora.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*{{IPA|/'plɛθərə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|plethora|plethoras}}
# (''Medicine, archaic'') an excess of red blood cells or bodily humours
#An excessive [[amount]] or [[number]]; an [[abundance]] (''+ '''of''''').
#:''The menu offers a '''plethora''' of cuisines from around the world.''
#:''El Guapo had a '''plethora''' of piñatas.''

====Synonyms====
*'''excess, abundance''': [[excess]], [[glut]], [[surfeit]], [[superfluity]], [[slew]]

